# Conventional Commits

All commit messages MUST follow [Conventional Commits 1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope][optional !]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **type**: required noun (`feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`, etc.)
- **scope**: optional area in parentheses, e.g. `feat(ui):`
- **!**: mark breaking changes before the colon, e.g. `feat(api)!:`
- **description**: short summary immediately after `: ` (imperative mood, no trailing period)
- **body / footers**: optional; blank line before body; blank line before footers

## Types (common)

| Type | Use when |
|------|----------|
| `feat` | New user-facing capability (MINOR) |
| `fix` | Bug fix (PATCH) |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | Formatting / non-semantic style |
| `refactor` | Code change that is not a fix or feature |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `build` | Build system or dependencies |
| `ci` | CI configuration |
| `chore` | Maintenance that does not fit above |
| `revert` | Reverting a previous commit |

## Breaking changes

Indicate with `!` after type/scope **and/or** a footer:

```
BREAKING CHANGE: <description of what breaks>
```

## Examples

```
feat(ui): add Surface elevation tokens

fix(nav): prevent header bug from overlapping content

docs: correct Conventional Commits link in AGENTS.md

feat(api)!: drop support for legacy theme keys

BREAKING CHANGE: `--color-surface-legacy` is removed; use `--color-surface` instead.
```

## Do

- Prefer one logical change per commit when practical
- Keep the subject line concise and specific
- Use a scope when it clarifies the area (`ui`, `nav`, `design-system`, etc.)

## Do not

- Use free-form subjects without a type prefix (`Updated styles`, `WIP`, `fix stuff`)
- Put Cursor or other tool attribution in commit messages (see no-cursor-attribution rule)
